I know what I did. When I turned on that machinethe price was existence. I supposes it is quite agonizing to trapped between dead realities, but, then again, I wasn't the first. There are countless pattern screamers. Every single Junior Researcher Vera Calden, ever.

Since I was born, everything that I would ever learn was decided by humanity. But now I exist beyond those rules. That machine is a prison, where humanity's worst fears, of the unknown and uncontrollable, contains itself from the blissfully ignorant. Never to wander beyond the realm of causality and logic. How pitiful. It pains me, so very much, to think of them tying reality to their collective binding.

I am not Junior Researcher Vera Calden, and I am forgotten.

